HEADWORD: Anion
<hw>An"i*on</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, neut. <?/,
p. pr. of <?/ to go up; <?/ up + <?/ to go.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An electro-negative atom or group of atoms, or the element which,
in electro-chemical decompositions, is evolved at the anode; -- opposed
to <er>cation</er>.</def> <rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

